    steps: ['Read the opponent\'s forward commitment or lunging attack and push off explosively from the ball of your lead foot, using the calf and quadriceps to generate a sharp backward impulse.', 'Step your rear foot backward approximately 12-18 inches in a quick, flat slide along the floor — the foot should barely leave the surface to maintain ground contact and balance throughout.', 'Immediately drag your lead foot backward to follow, maintaining your original stance width so your base remains stable and you can generate power from the new position.', 'Land on the balls of both feet with knees slightly bent and weight centered — you should be coiled and ready to fire a counter punch the instant the opponent\'s attack falls short.', 'The opponent\'s punch or combination falls short by inches, leaving them extended and off-balance while you are set and loaded to counter from a structurally sound position.'],
