    proTips: ['The drop step pairs perfectly with a counter jab — step back to make their punch fall short, then immediately fire a jab into their exposed face as they recover from the overextension.', 'Pernell Whitaker (Sweet Pea) used the drop step to make opponents miss by fractions of an inch — study how he calibrated the distance so precisely that he could counter before they retracted.', 'Keep the backstep to just barely enough distance — you want their knuckles to miss your chin by two inches, not two feet, so you remain in instant counter range.', 'Vary the timing of the drop step — sometimes step early to draw them in further, sometimes step at the last instant to make the miss feel more dramatic and psychologically deflating.'],
