    whenToUse: 'Use constantly between combinations, during neutral exchanges, and while reading the opponent. The shuffle maintains optimal distance through continuous tiny adjustments rather than large reactive corrections. It keeps you light on your feet and ready to attack, defend, angle, or retreat instantly without the startup delay of moving from a stationary position.',
    coachingCues: ['Tiny steps — never stop moving.', 'Stay on the balls, heels barely touch.', 'Ready to explode in any direction.', 'Every shuffle adjusts your position.'],
